Question 1:
Create a playbook which does not exit when ANY of the tasks fail.

Question 2:
Create a playbook which updates httpd and restarts sshd when the machine distribution is RedHat.

Question 3:
Create a playbook which creates a file with the content "Apache update has failed" in /tmp/apachestatus.txt
ONLY when updating apache fails due to any reason.

Question 4:
Create a playbook which:
installs and updates firewalld and httpd
creates a file "updatefailed.txt" in the /tmp directory if the update fails.
always restarts the sshd service irrespective of the output of the playbook. 
